Ask HN: Why there's no universal way to draw software architecture diagram?
text: Being a consultant I've seen so may styles of diagrams in the company. I realized even in the same company, people interpret the same diagram differently. It is very inefficient. A lot of time it is just a client, server, database, with some business logic etc. Why we cant have standardized pattern across everywhere? or does that exist? I also don't understand the concept of "reference architecture" because when i was software engineer in a big organization we never need a reference to draw diagram.
